author: brekke
msg: Patch from Steve Cohen:
After building Maven (instead of using distributed binary) I
can finally see the Checkstyle output without committing first, so could
REALLY clean it up this time.  The only things left in the new files are places
where checkstyle may be in error (as reported yesterday) or a few cases of
comment that are lines of actual sample FTP output longer than 80 chars which
I refuse to split.

author: brekke
msg: dlr's explanation for the url changes:
Pier is now using mod_proxy to ProxyPass/ProxyPassReverse connections
to Catalina through the Apache 2 running on nagoya.  This gives us
cleaner URLs, and is all around very cool (requires httpd.conf and
server.xml config).

author: brekke
msg: Patch from Steve Cohen:
This is a series of mostly cosmetic changes in response to the CheckStyle
suggestions and a couple of howling pieces of debugging junk that should not
have made it through - System.out.println() and the like.  A little more
significantly, two instances where exceptions were eaten were fixed -
in FTPFileList and MatchApparatus.
